  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6760.3 sitting right in the heart of massive negative gamma concentration (-49.7M at current level), dealers are being forced to buy this dip aggressively as hedging flows amplify the move lower. The breakout regime with -195.5B total GEX means dealers will continue buying weakness and selling strength, creating whipsaw conditions around these key levels between 6745-6765 where negative gamma is most concentrated. Watch for potential stabilization if we can reclaim 6765 (last major negative wall) or accelerated selling if we break 6745 support.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect volatile swings as dealers chase price in both directions around current levels.",
